ference I can see that im going to get between now and level 50 is an extra 50-60 hp a level due to the fact that offence defence and all the other relevant skills are capped.  Is this the actual case that the only real difference between a level 44 warrior and a level 49 warrior with the same equipment is that the higher level warrior has a few hundred HP?<br><br>Thanks in Advance <br><br>Krag<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukilaara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kilaara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 102<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/18/02 5:09:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=958.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.elchtom.de/Fantasy/f49.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Looking for info</span><hr size=1> Aggro between 1h and 2h.<br><br>There is no fix frontier. With the 2her you will make more damage and therefore more aggro. With the 1her you will hit more and therefore make more aggro.<br><br>It depends now on the difference between youre weapons if your 2her will be able to hold the aggro better than your 1her.<br><br>But don't forget one part. 5 Misses in a row with your 2her means a dead chanter. 5 misses in a row with your 1her means nothing.<br><br>The point to change to the 1her for holding aggro is the point where you fight mobs who can kill your chanter or cleric in 2 to 3 rounds of combat. This starts around Level 40 to Level 45. Then its without a meaning if your 2her makes more damage aggro cause then you need the constant flow of aggro and that is a point that a 2her is not able to generate so well.<br><br><br><br> <p><p><p><table border="0" cellpadding="3" ><tr><td><table border="4"  style="background-image:url