><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=958.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Looking for info</span><hr size=1> It really depends on the weapons your using at the time. For instance, a warrior using Claw of Lightning ( or primal ) and SoD will hold more agro then a warrior with say Epic 2hander, and the like. However, using say defiance and wave-crasher will yes hold agro, however a warrior using epic 2hander ( just using this two hander as an example ) will hold more agro over those said weapons. <br><br>Yes, Kilaara has a good point. 5 misses with a 2hander = dead chanter, or someone else that is important, where as 5 misses of a 1hander = nothing. It really all boils down to the weapons your using both 1handed and 2handed, and your skills in each I guess.<br><br>Lachmar Kikugami<br>Troll Paladin <p>/file<img src="http://junie.homestead.com/files/lachmar00.jpg" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ushikariiapoccalypse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shikarii Apoccalypse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>All in the reflexes</BR>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 1616<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/24/02 7:49:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=958.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Looking for info</span><hr size=1> **whoops had to delete that**<br><br>sorry  <p><center><img src=http://publish.hometown.aol.com/crushr85/myhomepage/new_vincent.jpg><BR>Shikarii T'Zaii -